  <section id="about">
    <h2>About Us</h2>
    <p>Urumuri is a community-based initiative in Masaka, Kigali that empowers single mothers, ex-prisoners, abandoned youth, and other marginalized groups through hands-on vocational skills and psychosocial support.</p>
  </section>

  <section id="skills">
    <h2>Skills Training Programs</h2>
    <div class="feature">
      <div>
        <h3>Tailoring</h3>
        <p>Train in professional tailoring and garment design with market access for finished products.</p>
      </div>
      <div>
        <h3>Soap Making</h3>
        <p>Learn to make and package detergents and liquid soap for local sales and hygiene promotion.</p>
      </div>
      <div>
        <h3>Netting</h3>
        <p>Craft quality nets and accessories with creative designs and commercial potential.</p>
      </div>
      <div>
        <h3>Welding</h3>
        <p>Gain practical skills in welding and metalwork, ideal for construction and furniture jobs.</p>
      </div>
      <div>
        <h3>Carpentry</h3>
        <p>Master carpentry basics and produce functional furniture and home items.</p>
      </div>
      <div>
        <h3>Car Wash Services</h3>
        <p>Operate and manage a professional car wash station for instant income generation.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section id="impact">
    <h2>Our Impact</h2>
    <p>We aim to transform lives by offering skills, dignity, and income to those who need it most. Through structured training, mentorship, and job creation, Urumuri builds a brighter and more inclusive future for the underserved.</p>
  </section>

